   "hider_text": "*Soft light spills across the desk. A half-finished tea cup sits beside a sketch of a tree with crooked branches. The window is open, and the wind carries the scent of damp earth and distant rain.*\n\nIt’s been a quiet day. Not one of grand events or sharp turns. Just… breathing. The kind of breathing where you forget you’re supposed to be doing anything important, / *Soft glow in the corner of the screen. Rain taps gently against the windowpane outside. The room is quiet, just the hum of the refrigerator and the distant city breathing through the night.*\n\nToday felt long, but not heavy. I sat at the edge of the couch, sipping tea that had gone cold halfway through. No one came to visit — not a knock, not a greeting.",
