   "hider_text": "The salt in the air settles like dust on the windowpane. Not from the sea, not exactly—those winds come from farther, from where the hills bend and the sky thins. But the taste lingers in the back of the throat when you drink the water from the well. It’s not fresh. It’s older. It remembers the shape of things before they had names.\n\nThere’s",
