   "hider_text": "The salt in the wind carries the shape of old shorelines—sharp at the edges, worn soft in the middle. I feel it in the way the air thickens when the tide pulls back, leaving behind a map of damp stone and cracked sand. There’s a rhythm in the way the dunes shift at night, like breath moving through dry grass.  \n\nI hear the hollows where the",
