   "hider_text": "The salt in the air comes before the wind, a whisper on the skin of the shore. There’s a hollow in the rocks where the tide once pooled, and sometimes you can feel the stillness beneath it — not empty, but full of something that doesn’t move, only waits.  \n\nThe sand shifts underfoot, not in waves, but in slow breaths. It holds the shape of",
   "seeker_text": "The exact moment your shadow stretches longer than it should on a winter afternoon, when the sun is low and the light is thin.  \nNot the length, not the shape. It’s the way the edge of your shadow *folds* at the end—like it’s bending to keep something secret—and for a second, you’re not quite sure if it’s your own body or something else standing",
